<title>UK: Procter &amp; Gamble applaud Cordiant plan.</title>
<headline>Procter &amp; Gamble applaud Cordiant plan.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Procter &amp; Gamble Co on Monday applauded Cordiant Plc's decision to demerge into three independently managed businesses.</p>
<p>&quot;From the client's point of view, we endorse Cordiant's demerger 100 percent,&quot; said Bob Wehling, senior vice-president at Procter &amp; Gamble.</p>
<p>The company is one of Cordiant's top clients, generating between five and 10 percent of the group's annual revenue.</p>
<p>&quot;Any move by an agency that motivates its staff better and is focused on client service can only be good news for all parties,&quot; he added.</p>
</text>
